```bash
# Find your recent experiments
beaker workspace experiments ai2/earth-systems --text "henryh"

# Output example:
# ID                          NAME                                    STATUS
# 01KEYN069TJM97JGNQ2TWRPH51  henryh/base_all_bands-train-366f1c59   1 failed
# 01KEYMZQQCW6SW71H8R7W2FD87  henryh/base_spectral-train-d2bc5c8c    running
# 01KEYMZA2EK7646BHTE0Y9TF6S  henryh/base_single_band-train-8e21bbbe succeeded

# Get details on running one
beaker experiment get 01KEYMZQQCW6SW71H8R7W2FD87 --format json
```

## Key Fields in JSON Output

When using `--format json`, key fields to look at:
- `status.exitCode` - 0 = success, non-zero = failure
- `status.created` - When experiment was submitted
- `status.started` - When it actually began running
- `status.exited` - When it finished (if done)
- `description` - Often contains progress info from wandb
